			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2023</a> paper:</span><br><i>A Reference GLL Implementation</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/AdrianJohnstone.html">Adrian Johnstone</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3623476.3623521">10.1145/3623476.3623521</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The paper delivers a reference implementation of the GLL parsing algorithm intended as a baseline tool for the community.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5f.html"><span class="tagL">T5F: Performance</span></a><ul><li> A key purpose is enabling fair performance comparisons of optimized GLL variants against a common baseline.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5e.html"><span class="tagL">T5E: Empirical Evaluation</span></a><ul><li> The work frames the implementation as an evaluation baseline for empirical comparisons across implementations.
</li></ul></li></ul>
